Donor Organism ID (Required): A unique ID for the biomaterial.
Donor Organism Name: A short, descriptive name for the biomaterial that need not be unique.
Donor Organism Description: A general description of the biomaterial.
SUPPLEMENTARY FILES: A list of filenames of biomaterial-level supplementary files.
BODY MASS INDEX: The body mass index of the donor.
ETHNICITY ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
ETHNICITY ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
GENUS SPECIES (Required): The scientific binomial name for the species of the organism.
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
BIOLOGICAL SEX (Required): The biological sex of the organism.
ALIVE AT COLLECTION (Required): Whether organism was alive at time of biomaterial collection.
AGE: Age of organism in Age units measured since birth.
AGE UNIT: A term that may be associated with a time unit-related ontology term.
AGE UNIT ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
AGE UNIT ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
DEVELOPMENT STAGE (Required): A term that may be associated with a development stage-related ontology term.
DEVELOPMENT STAGE ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
DEVELOPMENT STAGE ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOG: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
KNOWN DISEASE(S): Short description of known disease(s) of the organism.
KNOWN DISEASE(S) ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
KNOWN DISEASE(S) ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
COLD PERFUSED: Whether perfusion with cold fluid was used to help preserve tissues before heart stopped.
NUMBER OF DAYS ON VENTILATOR: Number of days on ventilator before death occurred.
VALUE ON HARDY SCALE: Value on 4-point Hardy scale cause of death classification.
TIME OF DEATH: Date and time when death was declared.
ORGAN DONATION DEATH TYPE: Type of death preceding organ donation.
NORMOTHERMIC REGIONAL PERFUSION: Whether entire body was perfused with warm oxygenated blood.
ALCOHOL HISTORY: Estimated amount of alcohol consumed per day.
MEDICATIONS: Medications the individual was taking at time of biomaterial collection.
SMOKING HISTORY: Estimated number of cigarettes smoked per day.
NUTRITIONAL STATE: Nutritional state of individual at time of biomaterial collection.
TEST RESULTS: Results from medical tests performed on the individual.
TREATMENTS: Treatments the individual has undergone prior to biomaterial collection.
HEIGHT: Height of organism in Height unit.
HEIGHT UNIT: A term that may be associated with a cell type-related ontology term.
HEIGHT UNIT ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
HEIGHT UNIT ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
WEIGHT: Weight of organism in Weight unit.
WEIGHT UNIT: A term that may be associated with a cell type-related ontology term.
WEIGHT UNIT ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
WEIGHT UNIT ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
Is living?: Yes if organism is living at time of biomaterial collection. No otherwise.

GENOTYPE: For example: DRB1 0401 protective allele; HLA-B*3901 allele
ETHNICITY: Enter one or more ethnicities, separated by a comma. For example: European; Hispanic or Latin American
ETHNICITY ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: For example: European; Hispanic or Latin American
GENUS SPECIES (Required): For example: Homo sapiens; Mus musculus
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: For example: Homo sapiens; Mus musculus
BIOLOGICAL SEX (Required): For example: Should be one of: male, female, mixed, or unknown.
ALIVE AT COLLECTION (Required): Enter yes if organism was alive at time of biomaterial collection, no if organism was dead, unknown if not known, and not applicable for ex vivo embryo. For example: Should be one of: yes, no, not applicable, or unknown.
AGE: Enter either a single value or a range of values. Indicate a range using a hyphen. For example: 20; 45-65
DEVELOPMENT STAGE (Required): For example: human adult stage; Theiler stage 28
DEVELOPMENT STAGE ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOG: For example: human adult stage; Theiler stage 28
KNOWN DISEASE(S): Enter 'normal' if no known disease. For example: type 2 diabetes mellitus; normal
KNOWN DISEASE(S) ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY: For example: type 2 diabetes mellitus; normal
CAUSE OF DEATH (Required): Determined from death report for human donor or from research lab for mouse. For example: Hypoxic brain damage; Sudden cardiac arrest
COLD PERFUSED: Enter yes if cold perfused. Otherwise, enter no. For example: Should be one of: yes, no.
VALUE ON HARDY SCALE: Enter: 0 for ventilator case, 1 for violent and fast death, 2 for fast death of natural causes, 3 for intermediate death, or 4 for slow death.
TIME OF DEATH: Enter the time in date-time format: yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ssZ. Supplying partial date is allowed. For example: 2016-01-21T00:00:00Z; 2016-03
ORGAN DONATION DEATH TYPE: Enter value for organ donors only. For example: Should be one of: Donation after circulatory death (DCD), or Donation after brainstem death (DBD).
NORMOTHERMIC REGIONAL PERFUSION: Enter yes if entire body (but not limbs) was perfused with warm oxygenated blood. Otherwise, enter no. For example: Should be one of: yes, no, or unknown.
ALCOHOL HISTORY: Enter the amount consumed per day using units such as alcohol units (10mL or 8g of alcohol) or drinks (14g of alcohol). For example: 3-6 alcohol units/day; 1 drink per day
MEDICATIONS: Enter the medication and dosage. Separate multiple medications with commas. For example: Naproxen 500mg/day; Citalopram 20mg/day
SMOKING HISTORY: Enter an estimated number of cigarettes smoked per day and for how many years. For example: 20 cigarettes/day for 25 years, stopped 2000
NUTRITIONAL STATE: For example: Should be one of: normal, fasting, or feeding tube removed.
TEST RESULTS: For example: lipid panel shows normal level of LDL (124 mg/dL); HIV, HBV, HCV: Negative
TREATMENTS: For example: Patient treated with antibiotics for a urinary tract infection; Patient treated with chemotherapy (Epirubicin, cisplatin, capecitabine) to treat stomach cancer
HEIGHT: Enter either a single value or a range of values. Indicate a range using a hyphen. For example: 160; 120-140
WEIGHT: Enter either a single value or a range of values. Indicate a range using a hyphen. For example: 60; 40-60
